[
  {
    "id": "169-2",
    "title": "169-2",
    "date": "2024-05-31",
    "medium": "watercolor",
    "dimensions": "",
    "tags": [
      "highway169"
    ],
    "description": "Another painting from my Highway 169 sketchbook. This is on the east side of the highway around LeSuer, MN. I originally named each painting using the lat/long of the location but the computer didn\u2019t like that so much.",
    "image": "169-2.png"
  },
  {
    "id": "169-3",
    "title": "169-3",
    "date": "05-16-2024",
    "medium": "Watercolor",
    "dimensions": "",
    "tags": [],
    "description": "This is from a small sketchbook I started using reference photos I have taken when driving back and forth between Mankato and Minneapolis. I always enjoy how the sun reflects bright on one edge of the metal silos. Even though it doesn\u2019t look like a four-lane highway, that is Highway 169 just beyond the fence. The geometric shapes of a farm site always intrigue me.",
    "image": "169-3.png"
  },
  {
    "id": "169-4",
    "title": "169-4",
    "date": "05-18-2024",
    "medium": "watercolor",
    "dimensions": "",
    "tags": [
      "highway169"
    ],
    "description": "There is an old, abandoned trailer just off Highway 169. Often I would think about pulling into the driveway and exploring around. On this trip I simply stopped and took a photo. The fields had just been plowed and the light and shadow was interesting on the end of the trailer.",
    "image": "169-4.png"
  },
  {
    "id": "169-5",
    "title": "169-5",
    "date": "2024-06-01",
    "medium": "Watercolor and ink",
    "dimensions": "",
    "tags": [
      "highway169"
    ],
    "description": "Driving South, right past the World\u2019s Largest (and most yellow) Candy Store, there is an open prairie littered with erratic boulders left-over from the glaciers. Every time I drive that way the prairie looks different and I see different configurations with the colors and the light.",
    "image": "169-5.jpeg"
  },
