  {
    "id": "8242Queen",
    "title": "8242Queen",
    "date": "2024-06-06",
    "medium": "watercolor",
    "dimensions": "8x10",
    "tags": [],
    "description": "This is the house I grew up in. Now it is beige. The car in the driveway is my brother\u2019s 57 Chevy. I painted this using a recent photo I took and was surprised later, when watching an old VCR tape, that all of the trees behind the house were small and hidden by the house. So, this is a juxtaposition of now as well as then. A lot of memories showed up while I was working on this painting. Mom teaching piano in the front room, digging up worms for fishing in the rhubarb bed next to the back door, the small and big hill in the backyard which was perfect for sledding in the winter. And, the upstairs window and my room just beyond it.",
    "image": "8242Queen.png"
  },
